    {
      "id": "1570a02d_140578d9",
      "file_path": "policy-management/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/drools/controller/IndexedDroolsControllerFactory.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 67,
      "message": "Optionally, may try to template this functionality into a method, since pretty much same as in the controller factory one, that could be reused by the controller and drools factories.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-15 23:49:49.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "318fd25f_2c8333ff",
      "file_path": "policy-management/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/drools/controller/IndexedDroolsControllerFactory.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 137,
      "message": "I guess, I am having trouble to see much benefit of introducing another\nway of doing things.  There are existing patterns in the code for example\nto override a LockManager or a PolicyController by using features, such as\nPolicyEngineFeatureApi.beforeCreateLockManager() and PolicyEngineFeatureApi.beforeCreate.\nThese don't require to maintain the ServiceLoader tables in each factory class.\nWe will have to add documentation describing this new approach (features are already\ndescribed at length in the documentation).",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-15 23:49:49.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "478aea03_49b81614",
      "file_path": "policy-management/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/drools/controller/IndexedDroolsControllerFactory.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 138,
      "message": "would have to check if controller is null, and throw exception, I think previous functionality ensured controller could not be null.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-15 23:49:49.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "bc16c9fd_72b60491",
      "file_path": "policy-management/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/drools/controller/IndexedDroolsControllerFactory.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 187,
      "message": "I would think, that similar to the work in the review in the PolicyControllerFactory,\nthis would be the place where it would make more sense to allow for a custom DroolsController,\nso not to skip the functionality above (right before the new).\n\nThere is going to be another implementation in this release that will require the same functionality\nthat tdjam uses.   For example, we have this epic that adds DMN controllers, ie. https://jira.onap.org/browse/POLICY-2642.\nThese controllers should be able to use this same mechanisms to provide their own controllers.\nNote that the DMN also uses maven coordinates, and kjars.\n\nThere may be other use cases that I could see may have similar needs, for example plain Aether-only based\ncontrollers.\n\nIn any case, feature hooks placed at this point, would seem to satisfy all the different needs, with\nor without maven coordinates, as any parameters can be passed, and the feature could ignore or not.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-15 23:49:49.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "593a6c08_e2272d89",
      "file_path": "policy-management/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/drools/system/IndexedPolicyControllerFactory.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 412,
      "message": "To preserve previous behavior, where will return a non-null object or exception (within constructor), check that builder.build() returns non-null.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-15 23:49:49.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "ec37b36d_4200c545",
      "file_path": "policy-management/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/drools/controller/IndexedDroolsControllerFactory.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 137,
      "message": "We did talk about this when we had a meeting to discuss this capability. The feature bus approach is very flexible, but it can be a bit chaotic -- each feature on the bus could use different criteria to decide whether to take control, and the winner is determined by who chose the lowest sequence number.\n\nIn this case, the extension is chosen by a string name, which is the value of 'controller.type'. There is still flexibility in how each individual builder works, but it seemed useful to nail down the way the builder is selected. Maybe there are other places in the code where this pattern would be useful -- it could become another extension mechanism in addition to 'OrderedService'. Perhaps it could be called 'TaggedService' or 'KeywordService'.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 743,
        "name": "Ralph Straubs",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "rs8887@att.com",
        "username": "rs8887"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-16 12:13:45.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "318fd25f_2c8333ff",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "cf2b4844_2ec9c7aa",
      "file_path": "policy-management/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/drools/controller/IndexedDroolsControllerFactory.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 137,
      "message": "is it difficult to do via the feature bus?  If not, I'd prefer to stick with that rather than invent another mechanism",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-16 19:32:56.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "ec37b36d_4200c545",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
